<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Sox Call Up Wells Just for Game </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	CHICAGO (AP) -- The Chicago White Sox recalled Kip Wells to pitch  
Friday's first game of a doubleheader and then sent him back to the 
minors after he beat the Texas Rangers. 
</P>
<P>
	Wells improved to 2-0 in two starts with Chicago with a 4-2 over  
Texas, but will most likely finish the minor league season with the 
Double-A Birmingham Barons. 
</P>
<P>
	``I know it's part of the game,'' Wells said. ``I didn't expect  
to walk in here and take over. They've got five guys in the 
rotation. Six won't do it.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Wells allowed one run on three hits and three walks in five  
innings. The right-hander has struck out 10 batters in 10 1-3 
innings. 
</P>
<P>
	Outfielder Darrin Jackson, who had been sidelined with a sore  
back, was activated from the disabled list to take Wells' spot on 
the roster. 
</P>
<P>
	Infielder Liu Rodriguez was optioned to Brimingham prior to the  
doubleheader to make room for Wells. 
</P>
<P>
	Wells, the No. 1 selection in the June 1998 draft, won his major  
league debut Aug. 2 at Detroit. He gave up two runs on six hits in 
5 1-3 innings before being optioned back to Birmingham. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
