<HEADLINE> Fernandez Expected To Miss One Start </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	MIAMI (AP) -- Florida Marlins pitcher Alex Fernandez is expected  
to miss one start after receiving a cortisone shot to treat 
inflammation in his right rotator cuff. 
</P>
<P>
	Fernandez, who pitched six innings in Wednesday's 6-5 victory  
over San Francisco, received the shot Thursday from Dr. James 
Andrews in Birmingham, Ala. 
</P>
<P>
	Fernandez won't throw for at least four days and will miss his  
scheduled start Tuesday at Los Angeles. 
</P>
<P>
	The right-hander, who turned 30 Friday, also received a  
cortisone shot in April. He has spent two stints on the disabled 
list this year while coming back from shoulder surgery that forced 
him to miss the 1998 season. 
</P>
<P>
	Fernandez is 6-7 with a 2.98 ERA.  
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
