<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Auburn's Robinson Pleads Guilty </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	AUBURN, Ala. (AP) -- Auburn wide receiver Clifton Robinson  
pleaded guilty to a lesser, misdemeanor charge in a case where he 
was accused of having sex with an underage girl, authorities said 
Friday. 
</P>
<P>
	Robinson had been charged with second-degree rape, but pleaded  
guilty to contributing to the delinquency of a minor, Lee County 
District Attorney Nick Abbott said. He was given a one-year, 
suspended sentence Friday and also ordered to perform 200 hours of 
community service. 
</P>
<P>
	Abbott said the plea agreement came at the request of the girl,  
who was visiting relatives in Auburn in March, and her mother. He 
said they wished to avoid a trial, which was scheduled to start 
Aug. 23. 
</P>
<P>
	Robinson was expected to be back at practice with the Tigers on  
Monday. He led the Tigers in receiving yards and all-purpose yards 
last season. 
</P>
<P>
	He pleaded innocent in late July to charges of having sex with a  
15-year-old girl. Coach Tommy Tuberville had suspended him from the 
team until the case was resolved. 
</P>
<P>
	Tuberville said Friday Robinson maintained his innocence of the  
original charge, but decided along with the other parties involved 
that the misdemeanor plea was the best option. 
</P>
<P>
	``Clifton has just gotten through with a very difficult  
situation,'' Tuberville said in a statement. ``It is time to move 
on and let Clifton get back to concentrating on school and his 
life.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Robinson has a probation hearing Jan. 27.  
</P>
</TEXT>
