	By reaching terms, Straka avoided an arbitration hearing  
scheduled Saturday in Toronto. 
</P>
<P>
	Straka, 26, was 11th in the NHL with a career-high 83 points  
last season and played in his first all-star game. He also led the 
Penguins with 11 points, including six goals, in their first-round 
playoff upset of the New Jersey Devils and 15 points in their two 
playoff series. 
</P>
