<HEADLINE> Indians Activate Kenny Lofton </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	CLEVELAND (AP) -- The Indians' impressive injured list was  
reduced by one Friday night as the team activated center fielder 
Kenny Lofton from the 15-day DL. 
</P>
<P>
	Lofton, sidelined since Aug. 7 with a strained right hamstring,  
is expected to be in the starting lineup for Saturday's game 
against the Baltimore Orioles. 
</P>
<P>
	To make room for Lofton, the Indians optioned third baseman  
Russell Branyan to Triple-A Buffalo. Branyan was hitting .211 with 
one homer and six RBIs, but had struck out 19 times in 38 at-bats. 
</P>
<P>
	Lofton could have played Friday night, but Indians manager Mike  
Hargrove decided to give him another day. Lofton is batting .305 
with six homers and 29 RBIs in 98 games. He has 24 stolen bases and 
entered Friday fifth in the AL with 89 runs. 
</P>
<P>
	The Indians have been banged up all year, and despite Lofton's  
activation, the club still has three regulars -- Sandy Alomar, 
Travis Fryman and Wil Cordero -- as well as two pitchers -- Jaret 
Wright and Dwight Gooden -- on the DL. 
</P>
<P>
	``I think we're starting to get healthy, and that's good,''  
Hargrove said. 
</P>
<P>
	Alomar, out since May 17 after undergoing surgery on his left  
knee, began a 20-day rehab assignment last Tuesday with Buffalo. 
Hargrove said the All-Star catcher could be back with Cleveland by 
the end of the team's seven-game homestand. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
