<HEADLINE> John Hinckley Takes Hospital Leave </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	WASHINGTON (AP) -- John Hinckley Jr. left Saint Elizabeths  
Hospital on Thursday for a short outing. 
</P>
<P>
	Under a recent court ruling the man who shot President Reagan  
and three others in 1981 can take short, supervised outings from 
the hospital. He was found innocent by reason of insanity in the 
shootings. 
</P>
<P>
	Hinckley was aboard a van that left the hospital at about 9:45  
a.m., followed by Secret Service agents. The vehicle carrying 
Hinckley drove to Alexandria, Va., where it stopped and turned 
around. 
</P>
<P>
	The trip was aborted before Hinckley reached his intended  
destination, Washington television station WUSA-TV reported. 
  	   	
