<CATEGORY> weather </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> The Nation's Weather  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	Showers and thunderstorms made their way across the Great Lakes  
and the Northeast Friday, while fair weather continued in the 
Plains and much of the West. 
</P>
<P>
	Thunderstorms stretched from Pennsylvania south across West  
Virginia and Virginia. There were also thunderstorms in northern 
Georgia, and in Michigan. 
</P>
<P>
	Afternoon showers and thunderstorms developed along the Gulf  
coast, the Southeast and the mid-Atlantic region, with large hail, 
damaging winds, and heavy rain. 
</P>
<P>
	Thunderstorms that rumbled across Wisconsin early Friday  
produced large hail and strong winds which downed trees. 
</P>
<P>
	Clear to partly cloudy skies are seen from the northern Plains  
in the Dakotas south across Nebraska, Kansas, Oklahoma, and 
southern Texas. Temperatures hovered between the 90s and 100s 
across the Plains. 
</P>
<P>
	In the West, the skies were clear to partly cloudy skies. Some  
showers and thunderstorms were seen across the Pacific Northwest. 
</P>
<P>
	Temperatures by early afternoon across the Lower 48 on Friday  
ranged from 100 degrees in Little Rock, Ark., to 33 degrees in 
Leadville, Colo. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
