<HEADLINE> 13 Paratroopers Hurt at Fort Bragg </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	FORT BRAGG, N.C. (AP) -- Thirteen Army paratroopers were injured  
Friday during a routine jump at Fort Bragg. 
</P>
<P>
	None of the injuries was life-threatening. Most involved ankles  
and knees, said Master Sgt. Mark Kalinoski. One soldier was 
admitted to a hospital. 
</P>
<P>
	The jump involved 280 soldiers from the 82nd Airborne Division,  
which is based at Fort Bragg. 
</P>
<P>
	A wind gust might have caused some of the paratroopers to make  
hard landings, though weather conditions were adequate to permit 
``a routine parachute jump'' when the exercise began, Kalinoski 
said. 
</P>
<P>
	``There was no indication of any type of parachute  
malfunctions,'' he said. 
  	   	
