<CATEGORY> financial </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Disney Reportedly Selling Fairchild </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	NEW YORK (AP) -- The Walt Disney Co. is reportedly trying to sell  
off some its assets, including its Fairchild Publications magazine 
division, to concentrate on its core businesses -- its studio and 
theme parks. 
</P>
<P>
	Conde Nast Publications and Hearst Magazines have been involved  
in bidding on the titles, a Disney executive told the New York 
Times for a story Friday. Conde Nast has reportedly offered $650 
million for Fairchild. 
</P>
<P>
	The news follows reports in The Los Angeles Times and other  
publications that Disney is looking for buyers for its professional 
sports franchises, baseball's Anaheim Angels and hockey's Anaheim 
Mighty Ducks. 
</P>
<P>
	Fairchild includes W, Women's Wear Daily, Los Angeles and Jane  
magazines. 
</P>
<P>
	The jewel of the acquisition would be W, a glossy fashion  
monthly that has become a general-interest magazine over the last 
four years. W has taken apparel advertising from magazines at both 
Hearst and Conde Nast. 
</P>
<P>
	Conde Nast, a division of Advance Publications, also publishes  
Glamour, Allure, GQ, Vanity Fair and The New Yorker, among other 
magazines. 
</P>
<P>
	In addition to Harper's Bazaar, Hearst Magazines publishes Town  
&AMP; Country and runs several newspapers and television stations. It 
recently announced it would publish Oprah, a lifestyle magazine 
with Oprah Winfrey as its brand spokeswoman. Hearst Magazines also 
joined Miramax Films, a division of Disney, in publishing Talk 
magazine, which made its debut last week. 
</P>
<P>
	The Fairchild group also publishes several trade magazines  
including Supermarket News, Brand Marketing, Footwear News and 
Children's Business. 
</P>
<P>
	Fairchild referred questions on the story to Disney. Disney  
spokeswoman Chris Castro declined to comment. 
</P>
<P>
	Disney stock, which has languished badly this year, rose $1.06 1/4,  
or 4 percent to $27.18 3/4 in trading Friday on the New York Stock 
Exchange. 

  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
