<HEADLINE> Inflation in Portugal Unchanged </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	LISBON, Portugal (AP) -- Portugal's consumer price index was  
unchanged in July, the National Statistics Institute reported 
Friday. 
</P>
<P>
	That left inflation at the consumer level rising at an  
annualized average rate of 2.8 percent. 
</P>
<P>
	The figures were in line with analysts' forecast and reflect a  
general lack of inflationary pressures, with significant easing of 
prices since the start of the year. 
</P>
<P>
	The report said increases in the prices of transport and hotels,  
and dining out in July were offset by a drop in the prices of food 
products and nonalcoholic beverages, clothing and footwear, and 
telecommunications. 
</P>
<P>
	Portugal's CPI had increased 0.2 percent in June and 0.1 percent  
in May. 
  	   	
