<HEADLINE> Kournikova Withdraws Due to Foot </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	TORONTO (AP) -- Anna Kournikova of Russia, the 12th-ranked  
women's player in the world, withdrew Friday from the du Maurier 
Open tennis championships, which starts Monday, because of a minor 
stress fracture in her right foot. 
</P>
<P>
	Kournikova injured her foot while practicing Friday and will  
likely be out for two weeks. 
</P>
<P>
	Kournikova, who lost to Conchita Martinez of Spain in the third  
round of last year's du Maurier Open in Montreal, is to be replaced 
in the main singles draw by Cristina Torrens-Valero of Spain. 
</P>
