<HEADLINE> Cher Shops While on Tour </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	CALGARY, Alberta (AP) -- Michael Wybrew couldn't believe his eyes  
when Cher dropped by his store before her concert. 
</P>
<P>
	The 53-year-old entertainer, on tour promoting her hit album  
``Believe,'' stopped in the Crown Surplus shop wearing dark glasses 
and a straw hat and spent about 45 minutes shopping on Wednesday. 
</P>
<P>
	``She bought a bunch of European military surplus stuff for her  
show and her son,'' said Wybrew. 
</P>
<P>
	``She was a really nice lady. She just poked around at stuff and  
made me try on everything,'' said John Cumming, the owner's 
brother-in-law who was told he is the same size as Cher's son, 
Elijah. 
</P>
<P>
	Other customers did not approach Cher, letting her shop in  
peace. 
</P>
<P>
	``Nobody asked for an autograph. Canadians are very cool. We  
just very nicely asked for one photograph because we didn't think 
anyone would believe us,'' Wybrew said. 
  	   	
</P>
