<HEADLINE> Big Movers in the Stock Market  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	NEW YORK (AP) -- Stocks that are moving substantially or trading  
heavily today on the New York Stock Exchange and Nasdaq Stock 
Market. 

</P>
<P>
                               *NYSE    	

</P>
<P>
	Walt Disney, up 1 at 27 1/8  
</P>
<P>
	The Burbank, Calif.-based entertainment giant, which has seen  
its earnings lag in the past year, has decided to sell its 
Fairchild Publications to focus on studio and theme park divisions. 
The Fairchild magazine division includes W, Women's Wear Daily, Los 
Angeles and Jane magazines. 

</P>
<P>
	Pfizer, up 3/4 at 34 3/4  
</P>
<P>
	The New York-based drug maker is halting development of a drug  
to treat nerve damage in diabetics. The company said a study showed 
little difference between its pill, Alond, and a dummy pill. 

</P>
<P>
	Cascade, down 1 1/16 at 11 15/16  
</P>
<P>
	The Portland, Ore.-based maker of lift truck attachments said it  
expects second quarter earnings to fall below forecasts. The 
company said profit margins have improved, but its European and 
North American business hasn't been as strong as expected. 

</P>
<P>
                              *NASDAQ   	

</P>
<P>
	Intelliquest Information Group, up 1 1/4 at 10 1/2  
</P>
<P>
	The Austin, Texas-based market research firm, is being acquired  
by London conglomerate Kantar Group in a deal worth about $42.5 
million. Kantar which owns market and media research companies, 
hopes to complete the deal by December. 

</P>
<P>
	Family Golf Centers, down 2 15/32 at 1 3/8  
</P>
<P>
	The Melville, N.Y.-based operator of golf courses said it does  
not have enough money to pay its debts. The company lost $1.5 
million in the second quarter. 

</P>
<P>
	Stewart Enterprises, down 3 9/32 at 6 25/32  
</P>
<P>
	Metairie, La.-based funeral products and services firm said it  
expects second quarter earnings to fall below last year's levels 
because of price competition and demand for lower-priced services. 
Demand for cremations also hurt business. 

  	   	
</P>
