<HEADLINE> Blue Jays' Wells Day-to-Day </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	TORONTO (AP) -- Blue Jays left-hander David Wells was scratched  
from his start Friday night because of a stiff back. 
</P>
<P>
	Wells was scheduled to pitch against Oakland's Kevin Appier in  
the opener of a three-game series between AL wild-card contenders. 
</P>
<P>
	Wells, who struggled with back problems during spring training,  
said his back stiffened up Thursday. Wells received treatment from 
a chiropractor Friday and tried to walk off the stiffness, but 
couldn't. He approached manager Jim Fregosi and told him he wasn't 
able to pitch. 
</P>
<P>
	``When I follow through that's when it catches,'' said Wells,  
who's listed as day-to-day. ``There's no use going out there and 
hurting it. Better safe than sorry.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Wells missed several starts during spring training because of  
his back, but said Friday that his current problem is not as 
severe. 
</P>
<P>
	Roy Halladay allowed six runs -- five earned -- and six hits in 4  
2-3 innings. He struck out eight. 
  	   	
</P>
