<HEADLINE> Director Scott's Home Burglarized </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	LONDON (AP) -- Thieves broke into the London home of Hollywood  
director Ridley Scott, punched his 94-year-old mother and took the 
Rolex watch from her wrist, a newspaper reported Friday. 
</P>
<P>
	Her screams alerted a nurse and Scott's ex-wife. As they fled  
upstairs to call police, one of the intruders chased them and 
warned: ``Don't make a noise or I'll kill you,'' the Evening 
Standard reported. 
</P>
<P>
	The women handed over rings and a necklace. When they managed to  
trigger an alarm, the robbers ran. 
</P>
<P>
	Scott, director of ``Blade Runner,'' ``Thelma and Louise'' and  
``Alien,'' was thought to have been away when the Aug. 4 attack 
occurred. He and his brother Tony Scott, director of ``Top Gun,'' 
own Britain's Shepperton Studios. 
  	   	
</P>
